{"id": 2786, "title": "Ticket #2786: Race condition in parallel universe can cause job to hang unstarted", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen the dedicated scheduler spawns a parallel job, it has a set of matches it wants to give the shadow.  After the shadow starts, it makes a daemon core call to the schedd, running a DC command to get the matches.  If, for some reason, one of the planned claims is released after the schedd makes it's decision and before the shadow asks for the claim, the shadow will block forever, as it will get a subset of the number of claims, and it will wait, trying to get the last ones.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2012-Jan-25 17:01</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=29217\">[29217]</a></span>: Documetn <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=2786\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('2786'); return false;\" title=\"Race condition in parallel universe can cause job to hang unstarted\">#2786</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2012-Jan-25 16:48</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=29216\">[29216]</a></span>: Fix race condition in parallel universe <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=2786\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('2786'); return false;\" title=\"Race condition in parallel universe can cause job to hang unstarted\">#2786</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr>